# Data Access Patterns

## Query Helpers — `db/queries` Directory

All database interactions must be encapsulated in typed helper functions inside `src/db/queries/`. Never write raw Drizzle queries inline in Server Components or Server Actions.

Organize files by resource (e.g. `src/db/queries/decks.ts`, `src/db/queries/cards.ts`). Each file exports focused, reusable async functions that accept only the arguments they need.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — src/db/queries/decks.ts
import { db } from "@/db";
import { decks } from "@/db/schema";
import { eq, and } from "drizzle-orm";

export async function getDecksByUser(userId: string) {
  return db.select().from(decks).where(eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId));
}

export async function getDeckByIdAndUser(deckId: number, userId: string) {
  return db.query.decks.findFirst({
    where: and(eq(decks.id, deckId), eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId)),
    with: { cards: true },
  });
}

export async function insertDeck(values: typeof decks.$inferInsert) {
  return db.insert(decks).values(values).returning();
}

export async function deleteDeckById(deckId: number) {
  return db.delete(decks).where(eq(decks.id, deckId));
}

// ❌ BAD — inline Drizzle query in a Server Component or Server Action
const userDecks = await db.select().from(decks).where(eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId));
```

## Data Fetching — Server Components Only

All data retrieval must happen in Server Components via query helpers. Never fetch data on the client.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — fetch via query helper in a Server Component
import { getDecksByUser } from "@/db/queries/decks";

export default async function DecksPage() {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  if (!userId) redirect("/");
  const decks = await getDecksByUser(userId);
  return <DeckList decks={decks} />;
}

// ❌ BAD — inline Drizzle query in a Server Component
const decks = await db.select().from(decks).where(eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId));

// ❌ BAD — fetching in a Client Component
"use client";
useEffect(() => {
  fetch("/api/decks").then(...);
}, []);
```

## Mutations — Server Actions Only

All inserts, updates, and deletes must go through Server Actions that delegate to query helpers. Never mutate via API routes or client-side calls.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — Server Action calls a query helper
"use server";
import { insertDeck } from "@/db/queries/decks";

export async function createDeckAction(input: CreateDeckInput) {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  if (!userId) return { error: "Unauthorized" };
  const parsed = createDeckSchema.safeParse(input);
  if (!parsed.success) return { error: parsed.error.flatten() };
  await insertDeck({ clerkUserId: userId, ...parsed.data });
}

// ❌ BAD — inline Drizzle mutation inside a Server Action
await db.insert(decks).values({ clerkUserId: userId, name });

// ❌ BAD — mutation in a route handler or client fetch
export async function POST(req: Request) {
  await db.insert(decks).values(...);
}
```

## Validation — Zod Required

All data passed into Server Actions must be validated with Zod before any database operation.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
import { z } from "zod";

const createDeckSchema = z.object({
  name: z.string().min(1).max(100),
  description: z.string().optional(),
});

type CreateDeckInput = z.infer<typeof createDeckSchema>;

export async function createDeckAction(input: CreateDeckInput) {
  const parsed = createDeckSchema.safeParse(input);
  if (!parsed.success) return { error: parsed.error.flatten() };
  // delegate to query helper
  await insertDeck({ clerkUserId: userId, ...parsed.data });
}

// ❌ BAD — no validation, or using FormData as the type
export async function createDeck(data: FormData) { ... }
```

## Rules

- All Drizzle queries must live in `src/db/queries/` — never inline them in components or actions
- Organize query files by resource (e.g. `decks.ts`, `cards.ts`)
- Data fetching belongs in Server Components — not `useEffect`, not `fetch()` calls in client code
- Server Components must call query helpers from `@/db/queries/*`, not `db` directly
- Mutations belong in Server Actions — not route handlers or client-side code
- Server Actions must call query helpers from `@/db/queries/*`, not `db` directly
- Every Server Action must define a typed input schema using Zod (`z.infer<typeof schema>`)
- Never use `FormData` as a Server Action parameter type
- Always call `safeParse` or `parse` before touching the database
